  <original-body>@@@map.resources :projects, :member  =&gt; {:team =&gt; [:get, :put]}@@@

Should work as mention in the corresponding [Guide](http://guides.rubyonrails.org/routing_outside_in.html &quot;Guide&quot;)

But it mixes up verbs:

@@@team_project GETPUT /projects/:id/team {:controller=&gt;&quot;projects&quot;, :action=&gt;&quot;team&quot;}@@@

With this route there is neither a GET nor a PUT request recognize correctly.

Changing it to :any works fine.
@@@map.resources :projects, :member  =&gt; {:team =&gt; :any}@@@ 

I'm using Rails 2.1.2 on Mac OS X 10.5 with shipped Apache2 and Passenger 2.0.3</original-body>
